description:
Convert REPLHistory from DefaultJinjaRender + custom render() to the new #[render(...)] attribute system. This is the poster child for the new architecture.

Location: crates/dspy-rs/src/rlm/history.rs

Current implementation:
```rust
impl DefaultJinjaRender for REPLHistory {
    const DEFAULT_TEMPLATE: &'static str = r#"..."#;
}

impl REPLHistory {
    pub fn render(&self, max_output_chars: usize) -> String {
        // Custom env setup with filters
        // Manual rendering
    }
}
```

New implementation:
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default, BamlType)]
#[render(default = r#"
{%- if value.entries | length == 0 -%}
You have not interacted with the REPL environment yet.
{%- else -%}
{%- for entry in value.entries -%}
=== Step {{ loop.index }} ===
{% if entry.reasoning %}Reasoning: {{ entry.reasoning }}{% endif %}
Code:
\`\`\`python
{{ entry.code }}
\`\`\`
{% set output_len = entry.output | length %}
Output ({{ output_len | format_count }} chars):
{% if output_len > ctx.max_output_chars %}
{{ entry.output | slice_chars(ctx.max_output_chars) }}
... (truncated to {{ ctx.max_output_chars | format_count }}/{{ output_len | format_count }} chars)
{% else %}
{{ entry.output }}
{% endif %}
{% endfor -%}
{%- endif -%}
"#)]
pub struct REPLHistory {
    pub entries: Vec<REPLEntry>,
}
```

Context handling:
- max_output_chars passed via ctx in render_messages_with_ctx
- No more #[baml(skip)] needed for internal state
- Template accesses ctx.max_output_chars

Delete:
- impl DefaultJinjaRender for REPLHistory
- The custom render() method
- Any special-case env setup for REPLHistory
